In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed a variety of topics, including the President's plan for rebuilding infrastructure in America, the release of the fiscal year 2019 budget, and the recent controversy surrounding former White House Staff Secretary Rob Porter. Sanders emphasized that the President takes domestic violence allegations seriously and supports due process. She also mentioned that the White House is looking at how they can improve their processes and procedures in light of the Porter situation. Additionally, Sanders mentioned that there is a nomination process underway for an office specific to domestic violence.